		<td><b>Blargg's NTSC filter demo for Windows</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have compiled Blargg's NTSC filter demo for Windows. This may be useful for previewing how an image may look as an NTSC screen.<br /><br />It's a command line tool. It works on test.bmp by default, but you can use an argument filename, or just drag a BMP onto the EXE.<br /><br />Original source code by Blargg, available here: <a href="http://slack.net/~ant/libs/ntsc.html" class="postlink">http://slack.net/~ant/libs/ntsc.html</a>

		
			<br clear="all" /><br />

